{
  "video_id": "E2KYqdyZcQY",
  "title": "What is Persistent Memory: Persistent Memory Programming Series | Intel Software",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 590.0,
      "end_time": 1090.0,
      "text": "Hi."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 1090.0,
      "end_time": 2820.0,
      "text": "I'm Andy Rudoff from Intel."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 2820.0,
      "end_time": 5770.0,
      "text": "In this video, I'll explain\nwhat persistent memory is"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 5770.0,
      "end_time": 7690.0,
      "text": "and why there's so much\nexcitement around it."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 7690.0,
      "end_time": 9648.0,
      "text": "Don't forget to watch\nthe rest of this playlist"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 9648.0,
      "end_time": 11277.0,
      "text": "on persistent\nmemory programming."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 14550.0,
      "end_time": 17190.0,
      "text": "Let's start by describing\nwhat persistent memory is."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 17190.0,
      "end_time": 19200.0,
      "text": "Sometimes called\nstorage class memory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 19200.0,
      "end_time": 20670.0,
      "text": "persistent memory\nis only recently"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 20670.0,
      "end_time": 22860.0,
      "text": "available on modern hardware\ndue to the emergence"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 22860.0,
      "end_time": 26700.0,
      "text": "of new memory technologies such\nas Intel's 3D XPoint memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 26700.0,
      "end_time": 28740.0,
      "text": "These new technologies\nallow products"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 28740.0,
      "end_time": 31710.0,
      "text": "with the attributes of\nboth storage and memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 31710.0,
      "end_time": 33660.0,
      "text": "These products are\npersistent, like storage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 33660.0,
      "end_time": 36990.0,
      "text": "meaning they hold their contents\neven across power cycles."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 36990.0,
      "end_time": 38790.0,
      "text": "And they're byte\naddressable, like memory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 38790.0,
      "end_time": 41950.0,
      "text": "meaning programs can access\ndata structures in place."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 41950.0,
      "end_time": 44550.0,
      "text": "But what really makes\npersistent memory stand out"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 44550.0,
      "end_time": 46620.0,
      "text": "is that it's fast enough\nto access directly"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 46620.0,
      "end_time": 48240.0,
      "text": "from the processor\nwithout stopping"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 48240.0,
      "end_time": 51030.0,
      "text": "to do the Block I/O required\nfor traditional storage."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 51030.0,
      "end_time": 52800.0,
      "text": "Performance is why\nthere's so much"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 52800.0,
      "end_time": 54300.0,
      "text": "recent excitement\nin the industry"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 54300.0,
      "end_time": 55920.0,
      "text": "around persistent memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 55920.0,
      "end_time": 58740.0,
      "text": "If you compare a modern\nNAND-based SSD which"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 58740.0,
      "end_time": 62130.0,
      "text": "plugs into the PCIe bus and\ncommunicates using MDM Express"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 62130.0,
      "end_time": 64140.0,
      "text": "protocol, you can\nsee the time it"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 64140.0,
      "end_time": 66840.0,
      "text": "takes to read a block\nis over 80 microseconds."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 66840.0,
      "end_time": 69900.0,
      "text": "Notice how most of the time\nis spent accessing the media"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 69900.0,
      "end_time": 71790.0,
      "text": "indicated by the blue area."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 71790.0,
      "end_time": 73710.0,
      "text": "The software stack\nis a small percentage"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 73710.0,
      "end_time": 75570.0,
      "text": "of the overall access time."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 75570.0,
      "end_time": 77910.0,
      "text": "We could work on making\nthe device driver faster"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 77910.0,
      "end_time": 79920.0,
      "text": "and the difference would\nbe hardly noticeable."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 79920.0,
      "end_time": 84270.0,
      "text": "The Intel Optane SSD also\nplugs into the PCIe bus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 84270.0,
      "end_time": 87270.0,
      "text": "but uses 3D XPoint, so\nthe time spent accessing"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 87270.0,
      "end_time": 89830.0,
      "text": "the media shrinks way down."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 89830.0,
      "end_time": 93000.0,
      "text": "Now notice that the overhead of\nthe software stack in the PCIe"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 93000.0,
      "end_time": 96330.0,
      "text": "protocol is a significant\nportion of the overall latency."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 96330.0,
      "end_time": 99420.0,
      "text": "To get the most out of\n3D XPoint technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 99420.0,
      "end_time": 102090.0,
      "text": "it now makes sense to tackle\nthe overhead of both software"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 102090.0,
      "end_time": 103110.0,
      "text": "and the interconnect."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 103110.0,
      "end_time": 105090.0,
      "text": "That's where persistent\nmemory comes in."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 105090.0,
      "end_time": 107420.0,
      "text": "By connecting the media\nto the memory bus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 107420.0,
      "end_time": 109230.0,
      "text": "the CPU can access\nthe data directly"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 109230.0,
      "end_time": 111690.0,
      "text": "without any driver\nor PCIe overhead."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 111690.0,
      "end_time": 114870.0,
      "text": "And since memory is accessed\nin 64-byte cache lines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 114870.0,
      "end_time": 116640.0,
      "text": "the CPU reads only\nwhat it needs to read"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 116640.0,
      "end_time": 118530.0,
      "text": "instead of rounding\nevery access up"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 118530.0,
      "end_time": 120540.0,
      "text": "to a block size like storage."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 120540.0,
      "end_time": 123990.0,
      "text": "You can see how low latency\na 64-byte read is here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 123990.0,
      "end_time": 127410.0,
      "text": "although I also show a 4K\nread for an apples-to-apples"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 127410.0,
      "end_time": 129539.0,
      "text": "comparison with the SSDS."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 129538.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131580.0,
      "text": "With persistent\nmemory, applications"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 131580.0,
      "end_time": 134400.0,
      "text": "have a new tier available\nfor data placement."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 134400.0,
      "end_time": 136920.0,
      "text": "In addition to the\nmemory and storage tiers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 136920.0,
      "end_time": 139140.0,
      "text": "the persistent\nmemory tier offers"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 139140.0,
      "end_time": 142200.0,
      "text": "capacities larger than DRAM\nand performance significantly"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 142200.0,
      "end_time": 143520.0,
      "text": "higher than storage."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 143520.0,
      "end_time": 146490.0,
      "text": "Applications can access\npersistent memory resident data"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 146490.0,
      "end_time": 150400.0,
      "text": "structures in place like they\ndo with traditional memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 150400.0,
      "end_time": 152580.0,
      "text": "This eliminates the need\nto page blocks of data"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 152580.0,
      "end_time": 155040.0,
      "text": "back and forth between\nmemory and storage."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 155040.0,
      "end_time": 157950.0,
      "text": "To get this low\nlatency direct access,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 157950.0,
      "end_time": 159780.0,
      "text": "we need a software\narchitecture that"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 159780.0,
      "end_time": 162510.0,
      "text": "allows applications to\nconnect up with ranges"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 162510.0,
      "end_time": 163890.0,
      "text": "of persistent memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 163890.0,
      "end_time": 166500.0,
      "text": "That's the topic of the\nrest of this video series."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 166500.0,
      "end_time": 169510.0,
      "text": "Re-architecting your\nsoftware will take some time."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 169510.0,
      "end_time": 172020.0,
      "text": "Get started right away by\nwatching this persistent memory"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 172020.0,
      "end_time": 173430.0,
      "text": "programming playlist."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 173430.0,
      "end_time": 175920.0,
      "text": "And don't forget to check out\nthe links in the description"
    },
